# Testing Standards

- Use Jasmine + Angular TestBed for component tests
- Test file naming: `component-name.component.spec.ts` (co-located with component)
- Each test must be independent — no shared mutable state between tests
- Query by role, text, or `data-testid` attributes (never by DOM structure)
- Use `fixture.detectChanges()` and `fakeAsync`/`tick` instead of hardcoded timeouts
- Assert specific content, not just existence

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
expect(compiled.querySelector('.task')).toBeTruthy();
setTimeout(() => { ... }, 1000);

// ✅ GOOD
expect(fixture.nativeElement.textContent).toContain('Buy groceries');
fixture.detectChanges();
expect(component.tasks().length).toBe(1);
```
